<body>
    <h1>T2 - Requirement Analysis Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"6a9b73d412f7" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-=
1.Introduction">1. Introduction</h1>
<p local-id=3D"8cdbee5cde95"><strong>1.1 Purpose</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"6562b58df78e">This document outlines the technical requireme=
nts and architectural considerations for implementing infrastructure automa=
tion using Jenkins integrated with AWS services.</p>
<p local-id=3D"30b2c8b3d794">The objective of this solution is to:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"000a151f-d15b-4421-96fb-52f4b8c29c18">
<li local-id=3D"82b85ee7-dcd2-4aef-9e95-8152e5b54b3c">
<p local-id=3D"6271a2d79197">Establish automated control over AWS infrastru=
cture components</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f83a7d80-9cac-48b2-8ebf-a0cfb3b5eb58">
<p local-id=3D"b6092061949d">Enable dynamic start and stop operations of Am=
azon EC2 instances</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fc41ff70-fe66-4294-81f4-67692469e587">
<p local-id=3D"3608e73db28a">Implement scalable management of Amazon ECS Fa=
rgate services</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"050e8bad-248d-47d2-b407-71a777fa50bc">
<p local-id=3D"d1fcd9e93362">Enforce secure, role-based access using AWS IA=
M</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"76c0d093-4af8-4de5-9c4d-49120bb68a8e">
<p local-id=3D"c9e8228746d5">Provide a structured framework for CI/CD-drive=
n infrastructure operations</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e65f347522bf">This document is intended for technical stakeh=
olders including CTOs, DevOps Engineers, Cloud Architects, and IT Operation=
s teams.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"cd073662-ed05-4623-8599-cb8965fd0f8d">
<p local-id=3D"8c01d207b966"><strong>1.2 Scope</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"7b2e0c4e3424">This implementation includes the following com=
ponents:</p>
<p local-id=3D"c049c72ebd45"><strong>Infrastructure Setup</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ac9d1ceb-4ebb-47ad-91da-9ee6ddc68f51">
<li local-id=3D"3d37ab18-3646-44a3-92cf-cb4a4f2757ef">
<p local-id=3D"36445574c725">Deployment of two EC2 instances representing D=
evelopment and Production environments</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9f1510dd-87a3-465e-822f-f5266ccbea81">
<p local-id=3D"ac4172c83620">Application of environment-based tagging for r=
esource identification</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c88454ff617d"><strong>Automation Platform Configuration</str=
ong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"d4412cc5-7ad2-4df7-bb1f-e1bb63bfd270">
<li local-id=3D"00ec90a9-d75a-42c5-8014-6bd097ea049c">
<p local-id=3D"206a9c34d69e">Installation and configuration of Jenkins on a=
 dedicated EC2 instance</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b3c77c6903b0"><strong>Secure Access Model</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"3c8bd553-1d35-49d9-8796-855f07892c41">
<li local-id=3D"de079870-b395-40b2-b507-c96e1e2b9242">
<p local-id=3D"d317e821e6fd">Configuration of an IAM role granting least-pr=
ivilege permissions to Jenkins</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f5275c14b29b"><strong>Automation Workflows</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"ce934ae89d4c">Creation of Jenkins pipelines to:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"25e4082f-b637-4702-831c-c318e4907bc2">
<li local-id=3D"60d8ea56-b939-48bd-8f97-3dbb4a229e73">
<p local-id=3D"6997e2ec13e6">Start Development EC2 instance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b51d215c-4360-4b0c-a313-b0c1c82a5d70">
<p local-id=3D"eb465fdf163a">Stop Development EC2 instance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d58be7e4-29be-40ca-8ceb-36976a4a3229">
<p local-id=3D"406dcd48e984">Scale ECS Fargate service (Bonus implementatio=
n)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"95c69febd7b6"><strong>Validation</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"5d8034de-60af-4def-bf80-c949f9028c4f">
<li local-id=3D"1227f506-bf05-4cc7-aa92-c77b39b47484">
<p local-id=3D"83d9ff8325a3">Verification of EC2 state transitions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"252e2f51-5718-46df-a1e3-07c19027a04e">
<p local-id=3D"98175738c6d3">Confirmation of ECS desired task count updates=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"22a92cd8c756">This document reflects the implemented solutio=
n only.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9a47951c-b56c-4ac6-92f2-c1fff9b6f272">
<h1 local-id=3D"6a813cf8ad44" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-2.Projec=
tOverview">2. Project Overview</h1>
<p local-id=3D"32f2929b27ac"><strong>2.1 Project Objectives</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"74a23bc37ddc">The solution is designed to introduce automati=
on into AWS infrastructure operations through Jenkins.</p>
<p local-id=3D"972cb742fdf2">Primary objectives include:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bd843f8c-e128-4e4b-ba8a-f9950bf3352d">
<li local-id=3D"0f42cfa5-c9e7-47fe-85a8-a6d439018620">
<p local-id=3D"a68681c2b2d9">Automating EC2 lifecycle operations</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b898bb5c-bca3-421a-ba9a-e3da5a915db9">
<p local-id=3D"b42b8dc786b7">Identifying resources dynamically using AWS ta=
gs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c3fa17a7-25bc-460a-bbf7-f7fcded8d03b">
<p local-id=3D"6ee34b7b6462">Eliminating hardcoded instance identifiers</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"c8cd546a-9cf8-4329-8653-77d122ac4a4e">
<p local-id=3D"6585815adb88">Implementing secure authentication through IAM=
 roles</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3bc916e9-6b6b-4c52-a5c0-3294bbe648d7">
<p local-id=3D"526ae2aa4bdf">Extending automation capabilities to container=
ized workloads</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0dbcb172-30a6-499e-a69e-5e5bdffac843">
<p local-id=3D"33c23b46367f"><strong>2.2 Business Goals</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"a006f3a6e4e0">The implementation supports key operational go=
als:</p>
<p local-id=3D"dea56ce74a09"><strong>Cost Control</strong><br>
Minimize unnecessary compute costs by shutting down unused development reso=
urces.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f3ce80b79fa4"><strong>Operational Efficiency</strong><br>
Replace manual infrastructure operations with automated workflows.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6c9fa71a77b6"><strong>Security Governance</strong><br>
Apply least privilege access control to maintain compliance and reduce expo=
sure.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c1e16a6ffc86"><strong>DevOps Enablement</strong><br>
Introduce CI/CD-based infrastructure control mechanisms.</p>
<p local-id=3D"84327c1489fb"><strong>Standardization</strong><br>
Adopt repeatable and consistent automation practices across environments.</=
p>
<hr local-id=3D"262df1ec-eec7-428c-acf0-06f82ced2643">
<p local-id=3D"bb46c8dc21f0"><strong>2.3 Background</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"0db8043c46c3">Prior to automation, EC2 instances were manage=
d manually via the AWS Console. This approach introduced:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"785caa48-252b-4de3-83c6-a37e58669f03">
<li local-id=3D"a46301e6-f316-4292-b1bd-54d3098e06a5">
<p local-id=3D"acb93dd25f33">Dependency on manual intervention</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"00f899d3-44d4-40b7-bc02-8a8595f4817e">
<p local-id=3D"0f85ee61190a">Delayed resource availability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"682b6ed1-dde6-41dd-a0aa-912ef1a31588">
<p local-id=3D"0e787d6f6652">Increased risk of unnecessary compute charges<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"faad41051ba7">By integrating Jenkins with AWS CLI and IAM ro=
le-based authentication, infrastructure management is transformed into a co=
ntrolled, automated workflow.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a53ef7b9524a">Amazon EC2 provides virtual compute resources.=
<br>
Amazon ECS with Fargate provides serverless container orchestration.<br>
Jenkins acts as the automation engine orchestrating AWS operations.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9bb5e414-ae83-4573-91cc-f1f96dc138be">
<p local-id=3D"67716f37312b"><strong>2.4 Constraints</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"7e14ea27d98a">The implementation adheres to the following co=
nditions:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c5f76b8a-a55a-45b8-9132-9065e806f2e7">
<li local-id=3D"e0c2f80f-8255-4965-98db-f83bcaecac8b">
<p local-id=3D"5dbdbb07774d">Use of Jenkins pipelines as the automation eng=
ine</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"41a6753f-d653-43e5-8e73-1a23df4abc91">
<p local-id=3D"43c287f3c571">AWS CLI as the command execution interface</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"e46e5ef1-2d07-4faa-b704-c2c52787dcb2">
<p local-id=3D"9939b305f0f2">IAM role authentication (no static credentials=
)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a95c69a8-3b5a-4227-aa91-1d77e0f6afef">
<p local-id=3D"124a83143b4f">Tag-based filtering for EC2 resource identific=
ation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ae237d79-aa34-4cea-bbbc-63cdd0d80fcc">
<p local-id=3D"ec77685b3958">Adherence to least privilege security principl=
e</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"d5919f932b21" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-3.Functi=
onalRequirements">3. Functional Requirements</h1>
<p local-id=3D"90d6242cfb94"><strong>3.1 Logical Flow of Operations</strong=
></p>
<p local-id=3D"65a1bf4bc7e3">Workflow:</p>
<p local-id=3D"dda79342f614">DevOps Engineer =E2=86=92 Trigger Jenkins Job<=
br>
Jenkins =E2=86=92 Execute AWS CLI<br>
AWS CLI =E2=86=92 Communicate with EC2/ECS<br>
AWS =E2=86=92 Update Resource State<br>
Engineer =E2=86=92 Validate Result</p>
<hr local-id=3D"24023e8c-2fff-4756-9ef2-83cb7c5a8790">
<p local-id=3D"cc33ae3d15e3"><strong>3.2 Defined Use Cases</strong></p><spa=
n class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence=
-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center=
" alt=3D"image-20260309-185453.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"4=
cb74258bbe681cc0dd9d903f08912ad59f0cf887af7a0594725445d97a2dcf8" data-image=
-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1784971308/i=
mage-20260309-185453.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1773082496041&a=
mp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"492" data-width=3D"982" da=
ta-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1843429494" da=
ta-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" d=
ata-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260309-185453.png" data-base-u=
rl=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=
=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1784971308" data-linked=
-resource-container-version=3D"7" data-media-id=3D"6ad4f90e-25dd-44f4-bced-=
ecb307c8339a" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"234"></span>
<p local-id=3D"b7548e493c6c"><strong>3.2.1 Use Case 1 =E2=80=93 Start Devel=
opment EC2 Instance</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"533ee2ecdae9"><strong>Objective:</strong><br>
Activate EC2 instance tagged with env=3Ddev.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1970978c15f4"><strong>Trigger:</strong><br>
Manual execution of Jenkins pipeline.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d24a0da12b2d"><strong>Execution Flow:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"686e0bf2-9b43-46fa-b562-0d1ededa7e34">
<li local-id=3D"656498fc-80aa-4ea1-9b07-4212c33817af">
<p local-id=3D"b9a8ee74a9a4">User initiates =E2=80=9CStart-Dev-EC2=E2=80=9D=
 job.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b142a69c-bb36-4acd-92b7-ed5315dc8fc8">
<p local-id=3D"79629836f20f">Jenkins queries EC2 instances using tag filter=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ec8977c3-ed6c-41ab-9f71-6058033defcf">
<p local-id=3D"a299420432a6">AWS CLI sends start command.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"21393a0b-7959-4129-bb55-1818c45e2889">
<p local-id=3D"5fed6f1cba4d">EC2 transitions to RUNNING state.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d02eb0bc-749d-4be6-8f60-6da2e008d6d3">
<p local-id=3D"fa5779e4f528">Pipeline logs confirm success.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"75fe47e1-98a2-4e7e-9d6b-343b616c0488">
<p local-id=3D"05d8d3a7f42a"><strong>3.2.2 Use Case 2 =E2=80=93 Stop Develo=
pment EC2 Instance</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"1e413a6f88b6"><strong>Objective:</strong><br>
Shut down EC2 instance tagged with env=3Ddev.</p>
<p local-id=3D"efc611c465dc"><strong>Trigger:</strong><br>
Manual Jenkins pipeline execution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"af04ead52cef"><strong>Execution Flow:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"834f2e83-d1f3-48fa-984c-264dfc460bbe">
<li local-id=3D"358e3746-df27-43af-bddf-53baaf16e0b2">
<p local-id=3D"7219e8447489">User triggers =E2=80=9CStop-Dev-EC2=E2=80=9D.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a75acf5e-03c0-4d64-b113-a80ad2d906c3">
<p local-id=3D"111acc6cc7bf">Jenkins retrieves instance via tag filter.</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"9acf0b3b-4f90-499e-bcb0-5978daa5afa1">
<p local-id=3D"87ccca77ef45">AWS CLI sends stop request.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ce8c780d-a555-49a8-99ae-094c6c83c33a">
<p local-id=3D"e5dff30ce4d7">EC2 transitions to STOPPED state.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c655fb66-1d23-41ff-8199-b43ec4dd31c0">
<p local-id=3D"c72380da4d75">Jenkins logs execution outcome.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"83a8f959-1e96-4389-8ba1-3acfad0e5cdc">
<p local-id=3D"d7bc22aed036"><strong>3.2.3 Use Case 3 =E2=80=93 ECS Fargate=
 Service Scaling</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f915cd319e5a"><strong>Objective:</strong><br>
Control ECS service availability through desired task count modification.</=
p>
<p local-id=3D"2d14d836521f"><strong>Execution:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"d2bd4c8d-941e-429e-8a41-c750b955241f">
<li local-id=3D"572424e3-27d7-4148-9218-13fd0d8b0f34">
<p local-id=3D"c9309146b71f">Desired count =3D 1 =E2=86=92 Service active</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2f3ed180-43c4-4cfc-a626-c0c5a9892d7b">
<p local-id=3D"52c4d47a7a2e">Desired count =3D 0 =E2=86=92 Service inactive=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c94e3efad1f1"><strong>Execution Flow:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"7c07c1e2-4944-4a17-8e92-eeb5dacf1f94">
<li local-id=3D"93c2cff7-cc13-410b-805e-41d9c8c67983">
<p local-id=3D"afbc7e7bd468">User triggers pipeline.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"71e1886e-8a77-423f-80cd-e48cbcf47202">
<p local-id=3D"a2c4c06dfeb9">Jenkins executes aws ecs update-service.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"82a713ce-44e2-4dce-b826-dccb47e82bca">
<p local-id=3D"3513dd9671dc">ECS adjusts desired task count.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f2660173-6e36-4902-8a1e-e564e108fa44">
<p local-id=3D"880ed312585c">Tasks launch or terminate accordingly.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"f36487ec-c02e-4edb-a0b2-3124d0f915ed">
<p local-id=3D"e55dee71e31e">Jenkins logs successful completion.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"8874c4d8-9ca4-477d-b3bc-46e64593c6f8">
<p local-id=3D"81cba187127d"><strong>3.2.4 Use Case 4 =E2=80=93 IAM-Based A=
uthorization</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"d0cb180300e7"><strong>Objective:</strong><br>
Ensure secure access to AWS resources.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b171a4637bfc"><strong>Process:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"4bb36b68-5ff5-4ae2-99c6-f69d8ab13cbe">
<li local-id=3D"e0e760d5-0b70-4a94-aeeb-6f3112466595">
<p local-id=3D"dd22dbbaee32">Jenkins EC2 assumes IAM role.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b980e72e-d380-43c0-a8c6-f58e3876676e">
<p local-id=3D"e14e31861cbd">AWS validates permissions.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ff346177-33f3-41d4-ace6-37f252985563">
<p local-id=3D"7d943f5dec77">Approved operations execute successfully.</p><=
/li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"4eb5ecde-dbf7-4440-8a95-04f0679625ae">
<h1 local-id=3D"ce46f794f8b6" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.Non-Fu=
nctionalRequirements">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<p local-id=3D"d37b1069fca8"><strong>4.1 Performance</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"4f17f7ca-185c-4bbf-839c-a8a9a890a297">
<li local-id=3D"e2a5e629-657c-4425-ac70-6d696dd42194">
<p local-id=3D"60da3b2447b6">EC2 start completion within 2=E2=80=933 minute=
s</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5df85509-a12b-416f-a6c5-b70c7e5354d0">
<p local-id=3D"5bca5637982b">Jenkins pipeline execution under 5 minutes</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"30cd6295-b0e1-4c98-806d-f0c0301fbf14">
<p local-id=3D"8aea66a6ae4e">ECS scaling reflected within approximately 60 =
seconds</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"88f70e85a46b"><strong>4.2 Security</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"7d52854d-d51a-437a-8947-6ff9130eba1e">
<li local-id=3D"43f5285e-ede2-48a3-bdc2-98637a5acbd5">
<p local-id=3D"fa48877fed7c">IAM policies restricted to required actions on=
ly</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"490460fb-99ef-4e6d-9928-28734a63f75c">
<p local-id=3D"0cf02d1b2604">No hardcoded AWS credentials</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"22dc552d-3b20-45ee-86ea-bdfd0d7796b8">
<p local-id=3D"b6e60ea19807">Jenkins port 8080 controlled via security grou=
p</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"67198c12-4490-4188-a15c-1dbaf3fda354">
<p local-id=3D"7ea169ab227f">Environment separation through tagging</p></li=
>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0050fe73-850b-4fa1-8520-a048b8de33af">
<p local-id=3D"5b7988117f79"><strong>4.3 Reliability</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"12017d169038">Pipelines must handle and log failures such as=
:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7fb557d4-ad31-4b77-8f0a-8fd5d8390d55">
<li local-id=3D"bd201a0c-1b0e-44e9-a23b-4091c264da9f">
<p local-id=3D"97b4a8eb1c90">Missing resource tags</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"507c6192-174c-4c5c-ada4-b4adfffedd77">
<p local-id=3D"4459366bc5f9">Permission denials</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9c723b16-2944-4b42-a2d4-4a92d7764931">
<p local-id=3D"bc2121277f25">AWS CLI execution errors</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6c7e36b81e02">Logs must clearly indicate execution status.</=
p>
<hr local-id=3D"9ccfe68e-769e-4ad9-bea1-15b02c9a65fd">
<h1 local-id=3D"460f60defcd1" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-5.Assump=
tionsandDependencies">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<p local-id=3D"ae2d8478dce8"><strong>5.1 Assumptions</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"53aeeb8c-f7d9-4a9f-bf44-d61efa9cb612">
<li local-id=3D"8cac6f45-9360-416b-9382-57e13afe924e">
<p local-id=3D"049d00306ff7">EC2 instances are correctly tagged</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4905bc5d-f455-4696-9268-f33bcd41ea75">
<p local-id=3D"193c70259e2f">AWS CLI is installed on Jenkins EC2</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8d0db66-5ea2-4cc9-ac31-c49b9392e0d7">
<p local-id=3D"87df6f0b5c96">IAM role is attached to Jenkins instance</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"1f0be174-e0af-4790-8867-2ea80cddf079">
<p local-id=3D"57f23330d856">Jenkins UI accessible via configured port</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"fdc54aec-5615-4b6e-8d22-2f577475f7eb">
<p local-id=3D"8e021fac1f85"><strong>5.2 Dependencies</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"6aa99dff-5aec-419f-a47c-74ec192baf37">
<li local-id=3D"78f6c5ed-7eae-4e13-bfb0-1e8a2ee0e638">
<p local-id=3D"7cbed7d02604">Active AWS account</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"68550e27-dd9c-4d15-84ed-ca5149509492">
<p local-id=3D"9b4ada3a2b11">Internet connectivity on Jenkins server</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"7d81358f-128c-4adc-b1d2-36edfb3c4ec5">
<p local-id=3D"f64cfbe6dae5">Proper VPC and security group configuration</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"4dd22e31-aa43-4521-b9d4-fceedb2f36b4">
<p local-id=3D"1fdeab2db00c">Correct AWS region settings</p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"1bf7b54199bb" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-6.RiskAs=
sessment">6. Risk Assessment</h1>
<p local-id=3D"30e72c471801"><strong>Identified Risks and Mitigation</stron=
g></p>
<p local-id=3D"8e78f805c1bf"><strong>Incorrect Tagging</strong><br>
Risk: Instance not located<br>
Mitigation: Validate tag configuration before execution</p>
<p local-id=3D"ea493d38d5fc"><strong>IAM Misconfiguration</strong><br>
Risk: AccessDenied error<br>
Mitigation: Confirm role attachment and policy permissions</p>
<p local-id=3D"c55c5c126c53"><strong>Security Group Configuration</strong><=
br>
Risk: Jenkins inaccessible<br>
Mitigation: Validate port 8080 access rules</p>
<p local-id=3D"8d96c97743c1"><strong>AWS CLI Absence</strong><br>
Risk: Pipeline failure<br>
Mitigation: Install and validate CLI before job creation</p>
<hr local-id=3D"7cb168e0-7ba4-40a1-91a1-4201e74b1428">
<h1 local-id=3D"2d37b89e2c44" id=3D"T2-RequirementAnalysisDocument-7.Glossa=
ry">7. Glossary</h1>
<p local-id=3D"d8881f7a9d9a"><strong>Jenkins</strong> =E2=80=93 Automation =
platform for CI/CD workflows<br><strong>EC2</strong> =E2=80=93 AWS virtual =
compute service<br><strong>ECS</strong> =E2=80=93 Container orchestration p=
latform<br><strong>Fargate</strong> =E2=80=93 Serverless container runtime<=
br><strong>IAM</strong> =E2=80=93 AWS identity and permission management<br=
><strong>Pipeline</strong> =E2=80=93 Automated workflow executed in Jenkins=
<br><strong>Tag</strong> =E2=80=93 Key-value identifier for AWS resources<s=
trong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
